explanation: This solution efficiently repeats string  a  and checks if  b  is a substring of the repeated string. It uses a while loop to repeat  a  until the length of the repeated string is greater than or equal to the length of  b . It then checks if  b  is a substring of the repeated string. If not, it checks if  b  can be a substring of the repeated string with one more repetition of  a . If still not, it returns -1. This approach has a high efficiency due to its simplicity and the use of the find method, which has a linear time complexity.

